Package: MethaMilk
Title: Integration and Analysis of Methane Emissions in Dairy Cattle from Automatic Milking Systems
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Amanda", "Robledo", , "arobcab@upv.edu.es", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tool for integrating and analysing enteric methane (CH4) and
    carbon dioxide (CO2) emissions recorded by sniffer sensors paired with
    automatic milking systems (AMS) in commercial dairy herds. The package
    covers cleaning and synchronisation of raw sensor and milking data,
    detection of eructation peaks in the CH4 signal, and computation of
    per-visit emission summary variables, providing a reproducible pipeline
    from raw records to interpretable emission phenotypes per cow and visit.
